File: Off switch Paul Cross/Flickr DURBAN - Power outages have hit several parts of KwaZulu-Natal after a storm damaged Eskom infrastructure.
Areas affected by the storm include Ladysmith, Escort, Nkandla, Hlabisa, Hluhluwe, Mtubatuba, Nongoma and Nqutu. The extent of the damage is still being assessed. READ: Eskom announces load reduction in four provinces Residents are being advised to treat all installations as live for safety reasons. Eskom is also urging people to stay away from low-hanging conductors and fallen structures.